Added aria-label="Delete material" to Delete IconButton

file_insights.code_context: Material table action column with Edit and Delete icon buttons

patterns_discovered.description: Adding aria-label attributes to icon buttons that already have title attributes
patterns_discovered.consistency: Both icon buttons in the action column follow the same pattern

patterns_discovered.description: Using both title (tooltip) and aria-label (screen reader) for redundant but complementary accessibility coverage
patterns_discovered.benefit: Supports both visual users (title) and screen reader users (aria-label)

gotchas_discovered.description: This is a straightforward accessibility enhancement with no apparent complications or edge cases

approach_outcome.approach_used: Direct modification of existing IconButton components to add missing aria-label attributes
approach_outcome.rationale: Added aria-label alongside existing title attributes to ensure screen reader accessibility while maintaining existing tooltip functionality

recommendations.suggestion: Audit other pages for similar icon buttons lacking aria-label attributes to ensure consistent accessibility across the application
Consider creating a reusable ActionIconButton component that enforces aria-label requirement for icon-only buttons
Verify that aria-label text matches title attribute text for consistency in user experience across different input methods
